programme.title: Move ! - La danse des algorithmes
programme.desc: La danseuse et choregraphe Sylvia Camarda explore le potentiel de l’IA à transformer radicalement les processus creatifs. Elle rencontre la choregraphe Blanca Li, pionnière en matière d’integration de nouvelles technologies dans sa discipline, et la choregraphe polonaise Irina Demina, qui travaille avec lIA à la preservation de danses folkloriques.

programme.title: Move ! - La danse irlandaise et ses pas bondissants
programme.desc: La danse irlandaise sest fait connaître aux yeux du monde avec le spectacle "Riverdance" en 1994. Mais quelle est l’origine de ces pas aux rythmes effrenes, et de cette posture peu habituelle des danseurs, bras raides le long du corps ? La danseuse et choregraphe Sylvia Camarda part à Dublin pour y evoquer les origines de la danse irlandaise.

programme.title: ARTE Regards
programme.desc: Le fentanyl est un puissant analgesique administre en cas de brûlures graves, de douleurs aigues postoperatoires ou d’origine cancereuse. Cet opioïde 50 fois plus puissant que l’heroïne est aussi utilise comme une drogue, notamment en Pologne où il a dejà fait des dizaines de victimes. Que faire pour lutter contre cette "drogue du zombie" ?

programme.title: Dis-moi ce que tu manges
programme.desc: De la Prehistoire à nos jours, l’histoire de l’alimentation eclaire l’evolution de l’humanite, entre traditions gastronomiques et enjeux sociaux. Un ambitieux voyage culinaire à travers les siècles.

programme.title: Merveilleuse planète
programme.desc: Dans le nord-ouest de l’Angleterre, au coeur de Lake District, les lacs s’etendent à perte de vue tandis que d’immenses montagnes, autrefois formees par l’action des volcans et des glaciers, se muent en collines verdoyantes. En toile de fond, de nombreux temoignages de la vie prehistorique revèlent de precieux indices sur la façon dont nos ancetres organisaient leur quotidien.

programme.title: Merveilleuse planète
programme.desc: Paysage côtier unique et dechiquete, la Causeway Coast, en Irlande du Nord, mele falaises abruptes et vallees verdoyantes. Sauvage et romantique, elle est celèbre pour sa chaussee des Geants, une impressionnante formation volcanique composee de 40.000 colonnes de basalte.

programme.title: Les promesses de la terre
programme.desc: Soumises aux vents, aux embruns sales et aux tempetes, les dunes se deplacent sans cesse, menaçant parfois densevelir routes et villes. Si nous les avons depuis longtemps fixees en plantant arbres et vegetaux, les vagues de chaleur, lurbanisation et les plantes invasives mettent aujourd’hui en peril ces paysages.

programme.title: ARTE Regards
programme.desc: Dans la Meuse, à Bar-le-Duc, des dizaines de salaries de l’entreprise Bergère de France ont pris le pari de sauver leur societe, une des dernières filatures industrielles de France, en la reprenant sous la forme d’une cooperative, une Scop. Avec cette aventure collective, ces employes espèrent sauver leur emploi et un savoir-faire industriel en devenant leur propre patron.

programme.title: De Gaulle et le Chancelier
programme.desc: En 1958, le general de Gaulle, revenu au pouvoir, invite le chancelier Konrad Adenauer à un tete-à-tete destine à sceller la reconciliation franco-allemande... Habile et savoureuse, cette fiction dans le secret des coulisses restitue l’intimite de la rencontre, avec un Jean-Yves Berteloot très convaincant dans la peau du grand homme français.

programme.title: Les parcs naturels portugais
programme.desc: Tour d’horizon des parcs naturels du Portugal. Dans ce volet : situe dans le sud-est du pays, le parc de la vallee du Guadiana s’etend sur plaines, rivières et forets mediterraneennes, offrant une nature preservee et une biodiversite exceptionnelle. Autrefois presque eteint, le lynx iberique reintègre peu à peu son habitat grâce à des mesures de protection ciblees.

programme.title: Les mille et un crabes de lîle Christmas
programme.desc: L’île Christmas, territoire australien au large de Java, est le paradis des crabes. Ces crustaces, qui se comptent par millions, ne limitent pas leur terrain de jeu aux plages: on en rencontre dans les sous-bois, sur les parcours de golf, dans les grottes et jusque dans les maisons.

programme.title: Les insectes, super-heros en minuscule
programme.desc: Presents dans le ciel, la canopee ou sous terre, les coleoptères constituent 25 % des etres vivants de la planète. Leur lutte pour la survie au fil des millenaires les a dotes dun corps extraordinaire surmonte d’une carapace protectrice. Desormais en peril, les coleoptères contribuent pourtant au nettoyage de la nature, certaines espèces se nourrissant des excrements d’autres animaux.

Amma shows them how to plant both bits of potato so that they can grow new potatoes.

programme.title: Bing Bunny
programme.desc: Bing discovers a hole in his favourite yellow wellies but he doesnt want to throw them away in the stinky dustbin.

programme.title: Oswald
programme.desc: Oswald tries roller-skating in Big City Park only to keep falling over. Daisy tries to teach him, and Johnny Snowman gives him a pep talk, but after Oswald falls into Fish Fountain, he is ready to give up. But then Madame Butterfly loses control of Catrina’s pram and it starts rolling wildly through the park, heading straight for Big Pond. Oswald sees the danger and, without thinking, roller-skates to the rescue!

programme.title: Oswald
programme.desc: Oswald and Weenie spend their very first sleepover with Henry but soon find that staying at someone else’s house can be very different. They have trout balls and spaghetti for dinner, which they would never have at home, and watch “Penguin Patrol” instead of “Sammy Starfish” – Oswald’s favourite TV programme. Best of all, they learn the Penguin Polka and realise trying out new things is fun.

programme.title: Bob the Builder
programme.desc: When Skye Sampson asks Bob and Team to create a beach motocross course on Fixham Beach, Bob is so enthused he decides to compete himself. But it’s been a while since he’s ridden his old bike and he wonders if it will even make it round the course. While Bob and Curtis work on the bike, word gets out that there is a mysterious entrant called the Masked Biker. Scoop and Muck become convinced that the Masked Biker is Leo, hiding his identity to take part even though he isn’t old enough to race.

programme.title: Bob the Builder
programme.desc: Mr Bentley is doing vocal warm-ups with the Spring City Rockets, and is about to begin rehearsals for his latest masterpiece, “A Pocketful of Pirates”. As Bob, Wendy, Leo, Dizzy and Muck arrive to renovate the hilltop theatre, Mr Bentley encourages them to join in the warm-ups. But Bob proves to be a hopeless thespian. As he confesses: I’m a builder, not a actor!” But Dizzy shows theatrical flair. When Mr Bentley has to run home and retrieve an important prop, he asks Dizzy to assistant direct. She’s so excited by the task that she accidentally tells Leo to use slow-drying cement instead of fast-drying cement as they begin paving a hillside track down to the theatre. Torn between two important tasks - the play and the build - Dizzy also messes up her directorial duties, telling Brandon to get his pirate props from the wrong box.

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You

Along the way Little Nutbrown Hare discovers how wonderful and different all his friends homes are. Will Little Nutbrown Hare still love his own home as much as he did?

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You
programme.desc: The series follows a warm father-son relationship that Little Nutbrown Hare decides he wants a clever long tail like his friends, rather than a short fluffy one. They help out by making him a long tail but all the results are either too tickly, bendy or flappy. When Big Nutbrown Hare spots his son from way across a grassy field everyone realizes that Little Nutbrown Hare’s little tail is clever in its own way.

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You

Will he be able to work up the courage to tell her what happened?

Felix suddenly stops “Look” he cries. “It’s a caterpillar” says Zim rushing towards it. They realise the giant caterpillar has lost her friends and looks very sad.

programme.title: Messy Goes To Okido

What better way to quench your thirst in Okido but to have a smoothie from the smoothie robot at the cafe. Messy, Zoe and Felix jump into Oki-doodle and whizz off to Okido City. When they arrive and order their smoothies there’s bad news! The smoothie robot has broken down and so the trio help to make smoothies until help arrives but they just can’t make them as fast as Smilford. A long queue forms outside the city as the thirsty people of Okido come for their smoothies!

Strawberry turns their apprehension into fun by daring her friends to stay out in the woods the longest! But soon, someone steals their marshmallow roasting sticks, the capture-the-flag-flags and the horseshoes. Lemon is sure that someone’s out to sabotage the campout! The girls build wacky monster-traps and capture... Huckleberry, who had gotten himself lost in the dark woods.

programme.title: Harry And His Bucket Full Of Dinosaurs

programme.title: Thomas And Friends
programme.desc: James hears Duck talking about the slip coaches they used on the Great Western Railway, which could be uncoupled at stations without stopping, and presents it to the Fat Controller as his idea - but he soon runs into trouble.

programme.title: Thomas And Friends

When they don’t come back, Thomas gets fed up and decides to take another load of troublesome trucks on his own and then there is trouble!

programme.title: Grisu
programme.desc: Sandro and Stella are preparing a surprise party for Davids tenth anniversary as captain of the fire brigade. But Fume unwittingly smashes the cake Sandro baked, and the firefighter doesnt have time to make a new one because he has to go on a rescue mission. So Grisu offers to bake one in his stead, helped by Stella. They immediately run into difficulties as the grocery shop is closed. They have to get their ingredients elsewhere – Fume at Gertrudes, Stella at Marias pizzeria and Grisu at Guellecs farm. This entails comic mishaps such as Stella running on a rollin pin or Grisu pursued by the black sheep.

programme.title: Grisu
programme.desc: Natureza is going to to the polar cap to conduct some studies. She needs someone to build an igloo for her while she sets up scientific instruments. Impervious to cold, Grisu accepts to come along and build the igloo. He quickly runs into comic difficulties: the snow he is to dig out to make bricks gets too hard, hes distracted by a playful sea lion, then hes trapped by falling icicles (and fortunately gets rescued by Natureza)… To top it off, as Grisu is almost done, a snowball thrown by the sea lion smashes on his head. Surprised, the little dragon lets out a flame that melts down the igloos top. But a firefighter never gives up!

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You

programme.title: The Lost Paradise, a portrait of Arvo Part
programme.desc: He is the most performed contemporary composer in the world. Nevertheless, he also rarely ventures out in public, keeps quiet about his music, feels at home in the forests of Estonia and generates therewith – perhaps involuntarily – the impression of a recluse, which is attributed to him again and again: Arvo Part.The Estonian composer, who will celebrate his 90th birthday on September 11, 2025, verily exudes even solely by his appearance an aura of a mystic or an ascetic. He himself says: “I am no prophet, no cardinal, not a monk, not even a vegetarian.” But he is without a doubt a devout man, who has been a member of the Russian Orthodox Church since 1970, and under pressure from the Soviet apparatus of power was forced to leave his native Estonia in 1980. Via Vienna he arrived in Berlin, which for the next 30 years would become his second home and also the starting point for his international career.“The Lost Paradise” is the first international documentary about Arvo Part. It is quite an astonishment that such a shy artist has given his consent to be accompanied by a camera for an entire year: In his native Estonia, travelling to Germany, Italy, and Japan, where Part received the Praemium Imperiale, the world’s most prestigious award in the field of music, in October 2014.The film is framed by the identically named stage production “Adam’s Passion,” featuring three key works by Arvo Part, which American director Robert Wilson brought to the stage in May 2015 in a former submarine factory, the “Noblessner Foundry” in Tallinn.

programme.title: Beskyddare av egyptens skatter
programme.desc: Arkeologerna soker efter ledtrådar till de mystiska kungarna som regerade nar Egyptens pyramiderna uppfordes. De soker i tunnlarna till Cheopspyramiden och under en ny grav som hittats nara tre senare faraoners pyramider. De hittar aven bevis på ett tempel som legat dolt i over 4000 år och som sprider nytt ljus over några av de maktigaste regenterna i det forntida Egyptens historia.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler

HSI Denver dyker ner i dark web for att spåra en last ecstasy som kopplas till flera dodsfall. Tullen i Newark konfiskerar en transport av den hallucinogena drogen khat till ett varde av 2 miljoner dollar.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler
programme.desc: Under standig uppsikt av de mexikanska kartellernas utsanda "spanare" hittar CBP 34,6 kilo meth i ett reservdack. CBP Newark hittar sju stulna fordon, varda 600 000 dollar, som ar på vag ut på internationella marknader. På JFK stoppar CBP stulna antikviteter från Mellanostern med ett marknadsvarde på 500–150 000 dollar, men ovarderliga ut ett kulturellt och historiskt perspektiv.

programme.title: Dranerade varldshav

Upptackten av sedan lange bortglomda skeppsvrak avslojar den sanna historien bakom deras eskapader – från Henry Morgans djarva rad mot spanjorerna till den legendariska Blackbeards sista veckor i livet – och berattar hur Karibiens unika position som en imperiernas motesplats gjorde det till det ultimata pirathavet.

programme.desc: Doug and Carrie find an old, unopened wedding present – a gravy boat – from Dougs third cousin Ron and his wife Marcia. However, because the check expired a year after the wedding, they ask Ron and Marcia to rewrite it. programme.title: Freud: Outsidern
programme.desc: En resa in i Sigmund Freuds liv och arbete i fyra akter - dar animation, drommar och insikter från ledande psykoanalytiker kombineras. Filmen utforskar Freuds upplevelser av marginalisering som jude i Wien under Hitlers uppgång och hur dessa formade hans teorier och personliga liv. Med ett nara perspektiv avslojar filmen nya dimensioner av Freuds arv med fokus på hans påverkan på psykoanalysen, judendomen och maktdynamiken av att vara en outsider. Israelisk dokumentar från 2025 av Yair Qedar.

programme.title: Politikbyrån
programme.desc: ”Det har inte varit ett enkelt beslut”, sa Tobias Billstrom nar han chockade svenskarna och avgick som utrikesminister. Med Billstrom som gast tar Politikbyrån dig med bakom kulisserna - vad var det egentligen som hande? Dessutom: Varfor ser Ulf Kristersson så glad ut nar han berattar hur litet det svenska regeringsplanet ar? Och hur fick fotboll och små vindruvor en otippat viktig roll i Nato-processen? Programmet gastas aven av dokumentarfilmaren Tommy Gulliksen som foljt Jens Stoltenberg i maktens korridorer samt Maggie Stromberg, forfattare till Nato-boken "Hogt over havet". Programledare: Karolina Skoglund.
